{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionGraph Neural Networks (GNNs) have emerged as a transformative paradigm in machine learning and artificial intelligence.",
    "The ubiquitous presence of interconnected data in various domains, from social networks and biology to recommendation systems and cybersecurity, has fueled the rapid evolution of GNNs.",
    "These networks have displayed remarkable capabilities in modeling and understanding complex relationships, making them pivotal in solving real-world problems that traditional machine-learning models struggle to address.",
    "GNNs' unique ability to capture intricate structural information inherent in graph-structured data is significant.",
    "This information often manifests as dependencies, connections, and contextual relationships essential for making informed predictions and decisions."
  ]
}